<subSubSection id="61ADDBE97442BF56CBF3FDD8FA24FAC5" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="290888627442BF56CBF3FDD8FC9CFDB0" blockId="10.[151,1437,325,1286]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56CBF3FDD8FEF0FE04" bold="true" box="[199,321,397,422]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is distinguished from the other Iranian species of 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CF0DFDD8FB27FE07" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1820" box="[1081,1174,397,421]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56CF0DFDD8FB27FE07" box="[1081,1174,397,421]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Phthiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having a short dorsal process on the first antennal flagellomere (
<figureCitation id="B18C94E77442BF56C94FFDE4FD0CFE68" box="[635,701,433,458]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1959,1981]" captionTargetBox="[218,1366,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[218,1366,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Phthiria fulva Meigen, male and female: a. male dorsal view; b. female head (lateral view); c. female head (dorsal view); d. female abdomen (dorsal view); e. the syntype of Phthiria fulva Meigen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837149/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
b) by the completely black habitus of male densely covered with black hairs (
<figureCitation id="B18C94E77442BF56CA10FD80FED8FE4C" box="[292,361,469,494]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1959,1981]" captionTargetBox="[218,1366,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[218,1366,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Phthiria fulva Meigen, male and female: a. male dorsal view; b. female head (lateral view); c. female head (dorsal view); d. female abdomen (dorsal view); e. the syntype of Phthiria fulva Meigen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837149/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
a). The females of this species have a black abdomen densely covered with short golden hairs (
<figureCitation id="B18C94E77442BF56CBABFDACFF53FDB0" box="[159,226,505,530]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1959,1981]" captionTargetBox="[218,1366,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[218,1366,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Phthiria fulva Meigen, male and female: a. male dorsal view; b. female head (lateral view); c. female head (dorsal view); d. female abdomen (dorsal view); e. the syntype of Phthiria fulva Meigen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837149/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
d), which is unique in the female of Iranian 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56C9F9FDACFC98FDB0" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1820" box="[717,809,505,530]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Phthiria</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="290888627442BF56CBF3FE4BFDE3FD67" blockId="10.[151,1437,325,1286]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">
<materialsCitation id="99DF823F7442BF56CBF3FE4BFDE3FD67" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1585189606" country="France" location="France" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="syntype">
In the Engel’s (1933) key, our specimens run to 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56C9EBFE48FBA3FD94" authority="Fabricius, 1805" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1805" box="[735,1042,541,566]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56C9EBFE48FCEBFD97" box="[735,858,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Ph. minuta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4D26F5937442BF56C855FE48FBA3FD94" author="Fabricius" box="[865,1042,541,566]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" refString="Fabricius, J. C. (1805) Systema antliatorum secundum ordines, genera, species adiecta synonymis, locis, observationibus, descriptionibus. C. Reichard, Brunsvigae [= Brunswick], xiv + [15] - 372 + [1] + 30 pp." type="book" year="1805">Fabricius, 1805</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="4D26F5937442BF56CF29FE48FB01FD94" author="Engel" box="[1053,1200,541,566]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" refString="Engel, O. (1933) Bombyliidae. In: Lindner, E. (Ed.), Die Fliegen der palaearktischen Region. IF (3). E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart, pp. 97 - 144." type="journal article" year="1933">Engel (1933)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CE03FE48FA2DFD97" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1804" box="[1335,1436,541,565]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56CE03FE48FA2DFD97" box="[1335,1436,541,565]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Ph. fulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CA6FFE14FE69FDFB" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1805" box="[347,472,577,601]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56CA6FFE14FE69FDFB" box="[347,472,577,601]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Ph. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Two female 
<typeStatus id="F60C36C07442BF56C942FE17FD69FDF8" box="[630,728,578,602]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56C835FE14FCD9FDFB" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1804" box="[769,872,577,601]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56C835FE14FCD9FDFB" box="[769,872,577,601]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Ph. fulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were checked by 
<bibRefCitation id="4D26F5937442BF56CF0DFE14FB51FDFB" author="Zaitzev" box="[1081,1248,577,602]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" refString="Zaitzev, V. F. (1997) On some type specimens of flies of the family Bombyliidae (Diptera) deposited in the museum of natural history in Paris. Entomological Review, 77 (3), 281 - 284." type="journal article" year="1997">Zaitzev (1997)</bibRefCitation>
when he visited Muséum national d’Histoire naturelle Paris, 
<collectingCountry id="51A0C8F27442BF56C995FE33FD40FDDF" box="[673,753,614,637]" name="France" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">France</collectingCountry>
. He verified the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CF56FE30FB7DFDDF" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1804" box="[1122,1228,613,637]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56CF56FE30FB7DFDDF" box="[1122,1228,613,637]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Ph. fulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CE21FE30FA24FDDF" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1805" box="[1301,1429,613,637]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56CE21FE30FA24FDDF" box="[1301,1429,613,637]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Ph. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Through the courtesy of Christophe Daugeron, photos of the 
<typeStatus id="F60C36C07442BF56C879FEDFFC1EFD00" box="[845,943,650,674]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">syntypes</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="B18C94E77442BF56C8F4FEDCFBB2FD00" box="[960,1027,649,674]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1959,1981]" captionTargetBox="[218,1366,193,1921]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[218,1366,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 5. Phthiria fulva Meigen, male and female: a. male dorsal view; b. female head (lateral view); c. female head (dorsal view); d. female abdomen (dorsal view); e. the syntype of Phthiria fulva Meigen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/837149/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
e) were checked and in our opinion, the synonymy of two species is correct.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="290888627442BF56CBF3FE84FEB0FC90" blockId="10.[151,1437,325,1286]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">
This is a Palaearctic species known from France and Belgium (Evenhuis &amp; Greathead 1999). 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CE21FE84FACFFD4B" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1804" box="[1301,1406,721,745]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56CE21FE84FACFFD4B" box="[1301,1406,721,745]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Ph. fulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from Iran for the first time. Recently 
<bibRefCitation id="4D26F5937442BF56C9FFFEA0FC03FCAC" author="Celechovsky" box="[715,946,757,782]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" refString="Celechovsky, A. (2011) First records of Phthiria canescens and Phthiria minuta (Diptera: Bombyliidae) from Slovakia. Klapalekiana, 47, 17 - 18." type="journal article" year="2011">Čelechovský (2011)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CF18FEA0FB27FCAF" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1804" box="[1068,1174,757,781]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56CF18FEA0FB27FCAF" box="[1068,1174,757,781]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Ph. fulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CFE4FEA0FAE1FCAF" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1805" box="[1232,1360,757,781]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56CFE4FEA0FAE1FCAF" box="[1232,1360,757,781]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Ph. minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) from Slovakia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="290888627442BF56CBF3FF68FB03FBA8" blockId="10.[151,1437,325,1286]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">
There are few host records of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56C9BAFF68FD5AFCF7" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1820" box="[654,747,829,853]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56C9BAFF68FD5AFCF7" box="[654,747,829,853]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Phthiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="4D26F5937442BF56C9CEFF6BFC09FCF4" box="[762,952,829,854]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" refString="Du Merle, P. (1975) Les hotes et les stades pre-imaginaux des Dipteres Bombyliidae: revue bibliographique annotee. Bulletin de la Section Regionale Ouest Palearctique (Organisation Internationale de Lutte Biologique), 4, 1 - 289." type="journal article">Du Merle (1975)</bibRefCitation>
summarized all information on the host of 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CBA3FF34FE99FCD8" authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" box="[151,296,865,890]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Bombyliidae</taxonomicName>
in which he listed the hosts for the three species of 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56C85AFF34FC7AFCDB" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1820" box="[878,971,865,889]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56C85AFF34FC7AFCDB" box="[878,971,865,889]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Phthiria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56C8EFFF34FAA0FCD8" authority="(Mikan 1796)" authorityName="Mikan" authorityYear="1796" baseAuthorityName="Mikan" baseAuthorityYear="1796" box="[987,1297,865,890]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pulicaria">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56C8EFFF34FBDEFCDB" box="[987,1135,865,889]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Ph. pulicaria</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="4D26F5937442BF56CF4AFF34FAB8FCD8" author="Mikan" box="[1150,1289,865,890]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" refString="Mikan, J. C. (1796) Monographia Bombyliorum Bohemiae iconibus illustrata. J. Herrl, Pragae [= Prague], 59 + [1] pp." type="journal article" year="1796">Mikan 1796</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
reared from 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CBA3FFD0FD09FC3C" authority="(Herrich-Schaffer 1854)" authorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" authorityYear="1854" baseAuthorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[151,696,901,926]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Scrobipulpula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="psilella">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56CBA3FFD0FE24FC3F" box="[151,405,901,925]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Scrobipulpula psilella</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="4D26F5937442BF56CA9DFFD0FD01FC3C" author="Herrich-Schaffer" box="[425,688,901,926]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" refString="Herrich-Schaffer, G. A. W. (1854) Systematische Bearbeitung der Schmetterlinge von Europa, zugleich als Tekst und supplement zu Jacob Hubner's Sammlung europaischen Schmetterlinge. Funfter Band, Regensburg, 394 pp." type="book" year="1854">Herrich-Schäffer 1854</bibRefCitation>
