<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56C93DFFA4FCC2FBA8" authority="Jaennicke, 1867" authorityName="Jaennicke" authorityYear="1867" box="[521,883,1009,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Poecilognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56C93DFFA4FD06FBAB" box="[521,695,1009,1033]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Poecilognathus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4D26F5937442BF56C98AFFA4FCC2FBA8" author="Jaennicke" box="[702,883,1009,1034]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" refString="Jaennicke, J. F. (1867) Neue exotische Dipteren. Abhandlungen herausgeben von der Senckenbergischen Naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 6, 311 - 407." type="journal article" year="1867">
Jaennicke, 
<quantity id="EE4F25877442BF56C80FFFA4FCC2FBA8" box="[827,883,1009,1034]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.74218" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" unit="in" value="1867.0">1867</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in the tribe 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56C8CEFFA4FB1FFBA8" authorityName="Hall &amp; Evenhuis" authorityYear="1987" box="[1018,1198,1009,1034]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Poecilognathini">Poecilognathini</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="290888627442BF56CBF3F843FEE2FB38" blockId="10.[151,1437,325,1286]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">
A few specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CA98F840FDA3FB8F" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1804" box="[428,530,1045,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56CA98F840FDA3FB8F" box="[428,530,1045,1069]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Ph. fulva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were reared from the pupa of the fruit moth, 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CF38F840FB3FFB8F" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1825" box="[1036,1166,1045,1069]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" genus="Argyresthia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56CF38F840FB3FFB8F" box="[1036,1166,1045,1069]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Argyresthia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CFF0F840FAC9FB8C" authorityName="Stephens" authorityYear="1829" box="[1220,1400,1045,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Yponomeutidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Yponomeutidae</taxonomicName>
) in a mountainous endemic microclimate densely covered by 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56C81CF86FFC27FBF3" authorityName="C.Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[808,918,1082,1105]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Juniperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56C81CF86FFC27FBF3" box="[808,918,1082,1105]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Juniperus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
trees. Lepidopteran cocoons were placed in a rearing cage from which six adult bee flies emerged. Two pupal exuviae were recovered for examination and are described below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="290888627442BF56CBF3F8F0FF58FAA4" blockId="10.[151,1437,325,1286]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">
The two tribes of 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CAB8F8F0FDB6FB1C" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1913" box="[396,519,1189,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Phthiriinae">Phthiriinae</taxonomicName>
can be separated based on the morphology of the pupal exuvium by the following key made by checking the pupal exuviae of 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56C9BBF89CFCE2FB40" authority="Meigen" authorityName="Meigen" authorityYear="1804" box="[655,851,1225,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulva">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56C9BBF89CFD47FB43" box="[655,758,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Ph. fulva</emphasis>
Meigen
</taxonomicName>
and that of 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56C8EBF89FFB74FB43" authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1863" box="[991,1221,1225,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Phthiria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulphurea">
<emphasis id="1BC354707442BF56C8EBF89FFBCCFB43" box="[991,1149,1225,1249]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">Po. sulphurea</emphasis>
Loew
</taxonomicName>
illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="4D26F5937442BF56CE5EF89CFF57FAA4" author="Hull" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" refString="Hull, F. M. (1973) Bee flies of the world. The genera of the family Bombyliidae. Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington D. C., 687 pp." type="book" year="1973">Hull (1973)</bibRefCitation>
:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="290888627442BF56CBA3F961FA24FAC5" blockId="10.[151,1435,1332,1383]" pageId="10" pageNumber="65">
Antennal processes united as a pyramid-shaped truncate tubercle; abdominal spines present on all except first segment.... 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CE74F961FA2AFAE8" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1913" box="[1344,1435,1332,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Phthiriini">Phthiriini</taxonomicName>
Antennal processes separate; abdominal spines restricted to first two segments.............................. 
<taxonomicName id="EEB7F3E17442BF56CFCBF904FA24FAC5" authorityName="Hall &amp; Evenhuis" authorityYear="1987" box="[1279,1429,1361,1383]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Poecilognathini">Poecilognathini</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
